# Trivalent-ligand / bivalent-receptor aggregation -- edition-2, fitting-ready NETWORK-FREE
# model for NFsim (method: nf). A trivalent ligand crosslinks bivalent cell-surface receptors
# into aggregates that grow without bound, so the reaction network is not finite and the model
# is simulated network-free. No `begin actions` block -- network-free models need no
# generate_network; the dose-response scan is synthesized from tlbr.conf (ADR-0028/0046).
#
# The model is from (primary):
#   Monine MI, Posner RG, Savage PB, Faeder JR, Hlavacek WS. "Modeling multivalent
#   ligand-receptor interactions with steric constraints on configurations of cell-surface
#   receptor aggregates." Biophys J 2010; 98(1):48-56.  PMID: 20074516  DOI: 10.1016/j.bpj.2009.09.043
# fit to the trivalent-antigen binding data of:
#   Posner RG, Geng D, Haymore S, Bogert J, Pecht I, Licht A, Savage PB. "Trivalent antigens
#   for degranulation of mast cells." Org Lett 2007; 9(18):3551-3554.  PMID: 17691814
#   DOI: 10.1021/ol071231z
#
# Provenance (unchanged model network): the trivalent-ligand/bivalent-receptor model of Monine
#   et al. (2010); the same fitting problem as BioNetFit 1 example 3 (Thomas et al. 2016,
#   Bioinformatics 32:798-800) and PyBNF 2019 corpus problem 11-TLBR (Mitra et al., iScience
#   2019). Upgraded to the edition-2 surface for the curate-pybnf-job corpus: the three fitted
#   parameters (alpha, K1, K2) bind to model ids BY NAME (ADR-0034, no __FREE aliases; the
#   nominals here are overridden by the optimizer) and the model carries NO actions block --
#   the dose-response simulation is synthesized from tlbr.conf.

# A model of trivalent ligand, bivalent receptor

begin model

# Reference:
# 1. Monine MI et al. (2010) Biophys J 98: 48-56. <-- model and fitting results
# 2. Posner RG et al. (2007) Org Lett 9: 3551-3554. <-- data

begin parameters

# Avogadro constant
NA 6.02214e23 # [=] molecules per mol

# fraction of a cell to consider in a stochastic simulation
f 0.001 # [=] dimensionless, from Table 1 in Ref 1

chi=1.0/f

# cell density
cellDensity 1.0e9 # [=] cells per L (1e6 cells per ml), from Table 1 in Ref 1

# volume of ECF surrounding a single cell (on average)
Vref=f/cellDensity # [=] L, from Table 1 in Ref 1

LTconc 7.0 # [=] nM

RTref f*3.0e5 # [=] molecules per cell, from Table 1 in Ref 1
LTref = LTconc*1.0e-9*(NA*Vref) # [=] ~4,200,000 molecules per cell, cf. Table 1 in Ref 1
RTconc = RTref*1.0e9/(NA*Vref) # [=] nM

# dissociation rate constants (settings are arbitrary)
koff 0.01 # [=] /s, from Table 1 in Ref
kr1=koff # [=] /s
kr2=koff # [=] /s

# FITTED (bind by id, ADR-0034): overall scale for the FL readout. Nominal = 1.
alpha	1

inverse_alpha=1.0/alpha # 1/alpha

# FITTED (bind by id, ADR-0034): free-ligand and crosslinking equilibrium constants (/nM).
K1	0.467 # [=] /nM, from Brandon
K2	87.03 # [=] /nM, from Brandon

kf1=K1*1.0e9*kr1/(NA*Vref) # [=] /(molecule/cell)/s
kf2=K2*1.0e9*kr2/(NA*Vref) # [=] /(molecule/cell)/s

end parameters

begin molecule types

L(s,s,s)
R(s,s)

end molecule types

begin seed species

L(s,s,s) LTref
R(s,s) RTref

end  seed species

begin observables

Molecules R_total R()
Molecules L_total L()
Species L_free L(s,s,s)

end observables

begin functions

lambda() (L_total-L_free)/(2.0*R_total) # [=] dimensionless, (0,1)
FL() inverse_alpha*(L_total-L_free)/(2.0*R_total) # FL = lambda/alpha or lambda = alpha*FL
# I am multiplying by the inverse of alpha instead of dividing by alpha
# to avoid a "divide by zero" error

end functions

begin reaction rules

L(s,s,s)+R(s)->L(s!1,s,s).R(s!1) kf1
L(s!+,s)+R(s)->L(s!+,s!1).R(s!1) kf2
L(s!1).R(s!1)->L(s)+R(s) koff

end reaction rules

end model
